---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { SITE, DISCLAIMER } from '../config';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Disclaimer"
  description="Honestly Profitable provides educational information only. Not financial, legal, or investment advice. Earnings are not guaranteed, individual results vary, and starting a business involves risk."
  path="/disclaimer"
>
  <div class="container container-narrow page-head">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Disclaimer' }]} />
    <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
    <p class="lead">{DISCLAIMER}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="container container-narrow page-body">
    <h2>Not financial, legal, or investment advice</h2>
    <p>
      Nothing on {SITE.name} constitutes financial, legal, investment, tax, accounting, or other
      professional advice. We are a publisher of educational information about business models. We
      do not know your personal circumstances, and nothing here should be treated as advice tailored
      to you. Before spending money or making decisions, consult qualified professionals (such as an
      accountant, attorney, or licensed advisor) where appropriate.
    </p>

    <h2>Earnings and results are not guaranteed</h2>
    <p>
      The startup costs, earnings ranges, timelines, and difficulty levels we publish are informed
      estimates drawn from publicly available data and reported operator experience. They describe
      what is <em>typical</em> or <em>possible</em> — not what you will achieve. <strong>Results are
      not typical and are not guaranteed.</strong> Most people who start a business earn less than the
      top figures shown, many earn nothing for a period, and some lose money. Business failure is
      common. Any earnings or income statements are estimates only; we make no representation that you
      will earn any particular amount, or any money at all. We show honest ranges precisely so you can
      plan for reality, not a fantasy.
    </p>

    <h2>No guarantee of accuracy or completeness</h2>
    <p>
      We work hard to keep information accurate and current, and each business page carries a "last
      reviewed" date. Even so, costs, regulations, taxes, and market conditions change constantly, and
      we do not warrant that any information is complete, current, or error-free. Always verify the
      specifics for your own market and time before acting.
    </p>

    <h2>You are responsible for your decisions</h2>
    <p>
      Any action you take based on information from this site is at your own risk. Starting a
      business involves financial and personal risk, including the possible loss of the money you
      invest. You are solely responsible for evaluating opportunities, complying with all applicable
      laws, licenses, permits, and tax obligations in your jurisdiction, and for your own outcomes.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      This site references and links to third-party websites and data sources for your convenience.
      We do not control those sites and are not responsible for their content, accuracy, or
      practices. A link is not an endorsement, and you access third-party sites at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2>Advertising and affiliate disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} is supported by advertising and may display ads through networks such as Google
      AdSense. Advertising is kept clearly separate from our editorial content and never influences
      our research or ratings. If we ever include affiliate links (links that could earn us a
      commission), we will disclose that clearly; regardless, such links would never change our honest
      assessment of a business. See our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for how
      advertising cookies work.
    </p>

    <h2>Consult a professional</h2>
    <p>
      For decisions with financial, legal, or tax consequences, seek advice from a qualified
      professional who can consider your specific situation. This site is a starting point for your
      research, not a substitute for personalized professional guidance.
    </p>

    <h2>Do your own research</h2>
    <p>
      Treat every page as a researched starting point — not the final word. Verify costs and
      regulations locally, talk to people actually running the business, and confirm the numbers for
      your specific market before committing money or time. Our full process is described in
      <a href="/how-we-research-businesses">how we research businesses</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="page-updated">Last updated: July 2026 · {SITE.domain}</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
